        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-muted">Last Updated: 2025</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect customer-related information, including names, images,
          phone numbers, payment details, and the starting date of the
          subscription.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>2. Purpose of Data Collection</h2>
        <p>
          The purpose of collecting this information is to help business owners
          manage customer subscriptions, track payments, receive automated
          reminders, and easily contact customers when needed.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>
          Data is stored in Firestore and Cloudinary. Business owners decide how
          long to retain customer data and can delete it when the customer
          leaves the service. We use Flutter Firebase Authentication for
          security but no additional security measures.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not share user data with any third parties except for essential
          services like Firebase, Cloudinary, and Railway for hosting.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>5. Business Owners' Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Business owners have full rights to view, correct, or delete their
          customer data. However, customers themselves do not have the ability
          to request access or modifications to their data.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>6. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          We do not use cookies, analytics tools, or other tracking
          technologies.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>7. Payment Processing</h2>
        <p>
          We currently do not handle payments directly or through any
          third-party services. However, we plan to integrate Razorpay in the
          future.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>8. Data Retention Policy</h2>
        <p>
          Data retention is managed by business owners. Once a customer leaves
          the service, their data can be deleted.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>9. Minor's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The app is specifically designed for business owners and is not
          intended for minors. Age restrictions apply.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2>10. Policy Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Users will be notified
          via in-app notifications.
        </p>
      </div>
